{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9b151326-fe83-4a3e-b9d1-ef3fd5584d5b","content":"In .NET MAUI, you use the **lifecycle events mapping** in `MauiProgram.cs` (or your app builder setup) via `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity =>\n        {\n            // Runs when the activity is pausing\n        })\n        .OnStop(activity =>\n        {\n            // Runs when the activity is stopping\n        }));\n#endif\n\n#if IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app =>\n        {\n            // Runs when the app enters background\n        }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;`\n- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#if IOS` preprocessor directives to keep platform code conditional.\n- The delegates receive the native platform object (`Activity` on Android, `UIApplication` on iOS), so you can call native APIs directly.\n- Other useful events: `OnResume`, `OnDestroy` (Android); `WillEnterForeground`, `WillTerminate` (iOS).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"157176fe-86bf-4675-a452-8462d49be1f9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI — specifically Android's `OnPause`/`OnStop` and iOS's `DidEnterBackground`. This is a general knowledge question, not a codebase task.","outputTokens":389},"id":"321c29f2-ee54-444c-bf47-ee5104a7c705","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:40:36.181Z","parentId":"b994676a-829e-48b6-b9dd-511f87fa5e72"}
